Zimbabwe Approves $146 Million of Investments, Herald Reports

-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 
2011-04-11T08:54:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/zimbabwe-approves-146-million-of-investments-herald-reports.html
Zimbabwe approved investments worth
$146 million in the first quarter of this year, up from $69
million a year earlier, the  Herald reported , citing figures from
the Zimbabwe Investment Authority.  Foreign investors accounted for $142 million of the
approved projects, the Harare-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Harare via Johannesburg at  ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  